{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ce75fae7-8bf0-48cb-b4f7-12534954002d","content":"The project doesn't exist yet in this workspace, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure to publish a C# MCP server as a `dotnet tool` on NuGet.org:\n\n### In your `.csproj`, add these properties:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>  <!-- CLI command name -->\n  <PackageOutputType>Exe</PackageOutputType>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/repo</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key steps:\n\n1. **`PackAsTool`** — this is the critical property that makes `dotnet pack` produce a tool package.\n2. **`ToolCommandName`** — the command users will type (e.g., `my-mcp-server`).\n3. **Pack it:** `dotnet pack -c Release`\n4. **Publish it:** `dotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg --api-key YOUR_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json`\n\n### Users install it with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\n### MCP client config (e.g., VS Code):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"my-server\": {\n      \"command\": \"my-mcp-server\",\n      \"args\": []\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe key thing most people miss is **`PackAsTool`** — without it, `dotnet pack` produces a library package, not a tool. Since your server uses stdio transport, it works naturally as a dotnet tool with no extra configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc58797a-0478-4826-897b-fb040e9f037d","outputTokens":550,"requestId":"AC07:121281:B4E148:E0E261:6A012DA9"},"id":"8bbd95af-cfc9-4a60-aac8-54ec6c9b09e0","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:15:31.890Z","parentId":"c8af4e7f-5b0e-42c3-bb1c-22f2934894eb"}
